channel.title: [Netbeans] Java files in a project
channel.description: How do i put Java files into a project for Netbeans? When i load client.java in it, it tells me it cant find this or it cant find that. Only because they are in other .java files like player.java, etc. Thank you.

item.title: [Netbeans] Java files in a project

item.description:

How do i put Java files into a project for Netbeans? When i load client.java in it, it tells me it cant find this or it cant find that. Only because they are in other .java files like player.java, etc. Thank you.
[/quote]

I believe there’s an option to create a project from existing source files.[/quote]

Yes, but when i click and use the folder, it doesnt show any .java files to edit in the sidebar.
